# Vifence CMS – Cursor Rules

## Core
- Target: Ban Tổng Giám đốc presentation quality
- Priority: Understandable > Consistent > Traceable > Actionable > Performant

## UI Consistency
- Sidebar: 220px fixed, never modify per module
- CameraGrid: single shared component, never create module-specific variants
- PlaybackPanel: single shared component
- EventList: single shared component
- Layout: Tier1 (KPIs) → Tier2 (Camera | Events) → Tier3 (Playback | Business Panel)

## Component Rules
- Reuse > Extend > Create New
- Never duplicate: CameraGrid, PlaybackPanel, EventList
- All components must be: Typed, Reusable, Testable

## Data Rules
- No hardcoded data in components — use services/ hooks/ store/
- All API responses must have TypeScript types
- No `any` type
- No direct API calls in UI components — always via service layer

## Performance
- React.memo for large components
- useMemo for computed data
- useCallback for event handlers
- Lazy load: Playback, Chart, Large Table

## UX
- No dead whitespace — fill or shrink
- No component overlapping Sidebar
- No duplicate data display
- Max 3 clicks per action
- Actions must be verbs in Vietnamese: Thông báo, Xử lý, Xuất clip, Tải xuống
- Lists > 20 records must have Search

## File Structure
src/
  components/common/   ← shared components
  modules/             ← module01 through module08
  services/            ← API service layer
  store/               ← Zustand stores
  types/               ← TypeScript types
  utils/               ← helpers
  hooks/               ← custom hooks

## Module Standard
- Module 01 is the reference implementation
- All other modules must follow Module 01 structure
- Only change business data per module, not layout/camera/events
